Single File Programming Question
Design a Browser Cache System



A web browser in Chennai keeps recently visited pages in memory to load them quickly. However, memory is limited, so when the cache is full, it removes the least recently used (LRU) page.



Design a data structure LRUCache that supports:



get(key)



return value if key exists


otherwise return -1


mark key as most recently used


put(key, value)



insert/update value

if capacity exceeded → remove least recently used key


 Both operations must run in O(1) time

Input format :
First line: integer capacity
Second line: integer q (number of operations)
Next q lines:

GET key
PUT key value
Output format :
For each GET operation → print result
Code constraints :
1 <= capacity <= 3000
0 <= key, value <= 10^5
At most 2 * 10^5 operations
Sample test cases :
Input 1 :
2 3
PUT 1 1
PUT 2 2
GET 1
Output 1 :
1
Input 2 :
2 4
PUT 1 1
PUT 2 2
PUT 3 3
GET 2
Output 2 :
2
Note :
The program will be evaluated only after the “Submit Code” is clicked.
Extra spaces and new line characters in the program output will result in the failure of the test case.

************************************
SOLUTION & CODE
************************************

// You are using Java
import java.util.*;
class Main{
    public static void main(String args[]){
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int capacity = sc.nextInt();
        int operations = sc.nextInt();
        sc.nextLine();
        
        Map<Integer, Integer> map = new LinkedHashMap<>(capacity, 0.75f, true);
        
        for (int i = 0; i < operations; i++) {
            String[] strArr = sc.nextLine().split(" ");
            // System.out.println(strArr[0] + ":");
            if (strArr[0].equals("PUT")) {
                int key = Integer.parseInt(strArr[1]);
                int val = Integer.parseInt(strArr[2]);
                if (!map.containsKey(key) && map.size() == capacity) {
                    int first = map.keySet().iterator().next();
                    map.remove(first);
                }
                map.put(key, val);
            }
            else {
                int key = Integer.parseInt(strArr[1]);
                System.out.println(map.getOrDefault(key, -1));
            }
        }
        
    }
}





